Author: dinerdrive
Text: yeah i always hated days when i would choose to eat something "unhealthy" and nothing else. and then people would comment on how unhealthy it was. like bitch this is the only thing i'm eating today and you're about to put me off of it! i know that eating a 300cal peanut butter cookie doesn't have much in the way of nutrition but damn.  i don't do this anymore as i think i've gotten sort of orthorexic but it always made me want to cry and ruined my appetite for whatever i had planned out

Author: satanic-sloth
Text: i know your pain. my mom is the exact same way. she too is clinically obese and almost every day comments on my eating habits. like yesterday when all i had eaten was a square of chocolate and when she offered me food i said my stomach hurt. “maybe it’s because you’re always eating junk” says the woman standing next to two empty pizza boxes.
